‚óè Explain difference between JPA and Hibernate.

1) JPA
      1-JPA stand for Java persistence API.
      2-JPA is a Standard API for all the ORM s/w.
      3-JPA is responsible for mapping relational databases in java application.
      4-JPA is defined under the javax.persistece package.
      5-JPA is the java specification and not the implementation.
      
      
2)Hibernate
           1-Hibernate is an ORM tool used for saving the state of the java object in the DB.
           2-Hibernate is defined under org.hibernate package.
           3-Hibernate is an implementation of JPA and uses common standards of JPA.
           4-it is used to map java data types with databases tables and SQL data types.      